caption: Cool little place. Can take the kids in and have a cold beer and great, fall off the bone ribs
10/10 food was amazing, service was amazing, I would definitely recommend!!
Ok.... the food was good.  We had an issue with the potatoes not being done...BUT they went above and beyond to make it right. That’s what gave them 5 stars.... GREAT SERVICE!
Great place, amazing burgers, and even better people!
This was delicious better than anything back home for sure
Hands down one of the best burgers I ever ate
Still the best Hamburger you can expect to get on Bourbon street....peanut butter bacon with cheddar and pepper jack. Make it your last stop for the night. Its ridiculously good.
Use to have fantastic sunday crawfish boils .
New name same great food better service
The peanutbutter bacon burger is incredible!
Thank God there is Port St. Peter now.  No more meatloaf sandwiches, cleaner, better service and staff at the new business at the location of the former Yo Mama's
You can't not go here for a burger if you're on Bourbon.
They have since changed the name. But the food and service was great. Not too crowded seeing where they are. And they have the biggest baked potatoes definitely recommend.

Very mediocre food,very high price at $14 a burger. Burger was over cooked ordered medrare got medwell and didn't even melt the cheese on it. Told the bartender and they didn't care and said they like the burgers. Not to mention advertised it like the food hasnt changed. Will never return. Also they false advertise like yo mama's still exists and they're gone and the bar took over and they suck. I'm also a professional cook.
This place is now called port St Peter! The name is the only thing that has changed the food is same and amazing!

I'm a transplant whose been to yo mamas a dozen or so times over the last 3 years.  Loved the yo mamas burgers and baked potatoes.  Yesterday was my first visit since the ownership change.  My girlfriend and I went craving their burger. In short this establishment is not yo mamas.  The restaurant is void of the personality it once was.  It has no personality.  The staff seems to awkwardly recognize it as well.  Althoigh we came because we were craving the cheddar burger, we  almost didn't order.  But the bartender told us the cooks were still the same.  By the way, the place is now called port of St. Peter's or St. Peter's Port.  We ordered 2 cheddar burgers and baked potatoes.  We were told there were no baked potatoes ready.  That stuff happens but it never happened at yo mamas.  We subbed the Mac n cheese.  The burger was disappointing.  It was laden with garlic and other unknown spices that overpowered the taste of the beef.  The patty was dense. The bun was fresh but sweet.  Overall the burger is average at best.  For those that knew yo mamas, they had an awesome burger.  One of the best in Nola.... The Mac n cheese was unremarkable.  Overall our experience was marked negatively in part by the claims of the staff that the food was the same as yo mamas.  It is clearly not.  And that claim will hurt them with anyone who ate at yo mamas.  Like some of the other locals posted here, we will not go back.  The new restaurant may be trying to cater to the more transient crowd.  And I wish them well.
It isn't yo momma's anymore and despite the sign food isn't better.
Amazing food. I dream about this food! The staff is friendly too!!
Best burger you will ever eat.
Good food liked the old name better but the food is still on point
I cannot imagine giving 5 stars to a bar, but there it is.  If you love hamburgers you will love this bar.  If you love bars you will love this bar.  And you can stumble over here from Pat O's.

Usually crowded and bartenders are sometimes cranky. Probably from dealing with drunk tourists. But they have an awesome burger menu. Be sure to give the peanut butter burger a chance. Sounds weird, yet quite tasty.....

Yo mammas used to be good. Since they closed the new atmosphere is ok. They claim to have the same menu however it's a fraction of the taste. I tried to stop in to get a burger with my dog and they kicked me out. There was NO ONE else in the place.  The lady bartender that kicked me out had no personality. I use to go once a week, I'll never go back again.

Sadly, this dive joint with incredible food is now closed. We tried to go last weekend while in Nola and it was padlocked. We asked two guys loading up a pickup, and they said it was done for good. It will be missed.
Permanently closed.
Great burgers. Best in French quarter!

Came here for a quick dinner. The place is more of a bar then anything else. They pretty much serve only burgers and a few other things. There was no wait when we got there and we sat at the bar. Service is prompt and good. We had the peanut butter burger, mushroom burger, and the gumbo. Burgers were very good and the gumbo was not bad at all. It was the cheapest meal thus far in nola. I would definitely come back again.
Very good service, good food, good price!
#1 Bleu Shroom burger & Bleu Shroom veggie burger!!!
Cozy dive with good bartenders and tasty burgers.
Got the Bacon Burger and it was amazing along with the Mac n Cheese. Not busy so somewhat private. I would recommend going there for a nice drink and delicious food.

Called to get an itemized receipt for one of our Board Members so he wouldn't have to call. Spoke to a very rude waitress. When I tried to give her additional information on the receipt, she informed me, "I'm in the middle of a lunch rush."  I didn't realize that a customer who had already paid would not longer be important to her.  I certainly wouldn't eat here again. And I wouldn't recommend anyone else do so, either. :)

The food is pretty good. Very generous with the amount of food you get. The price was very nice too, I think it was our best value for a meal we had the whole time in New Orleans. The service however was not that great. We were not given a menu to look at or asked for our drinks until we had been sitting at the bar for almost ten minutes. Once we got our food we had no utensils to eat said food with. I had to wave a bartender down to get utensils. Mind you this was a Sunday night and though they were steady they were not too busy to ignore customers. I did like the food too bad I won't be going back due to poor customer service.
Place rocks & best burger I've found - Bacon, Bacon, Bacon. Baked potato too!
The best burger in New Orleans second to none! First stop every visit.
We go every single time we're in NOLA. Love love love this place! Go listen to jazz across the street!
This is my favorite bar in NOLA! AMAZING FOOD, DRINKS AND SERVICE!

Tried this dive bar and grill twice, loved the food! Drinks reasonable for the area and staff was nice which is increasingly rare in NOLA. Could use a deep cleaning but this close to Burbon St it's almost fitting to be dirty. Definitely great place to go to in the quarter. And yes the peanut butter burger is amazing!
The peanut butter burger was alright. I've had their other burgers and they are amazing!

Found this place online, and the food sounded amazing. I ended up at the bar upstairs - v chill, private feeling place. The downstairs area seemed more the volume of the rest of the street. The burger was amazing after all, even if the beer selection was a bit limited.  Don't go here for the beers.  Obviously.   Good times.
Hands-down the best burgers I've found in Nola. The restroom is neat too.
Good Burgers and nice bar.
Huge burgers with Awesome flavor! The best burger I've ever eaten! My husband had the Mega Burger (Texas BBQ) and it covered the entire plate, I had Mushroom & Swiss Burger.

Came in about 1:30 AM after a long 6 hour drive. Bartender/waitress was really sweet and friendly. I had the "Taste of Yo Mama" which was great, and my husband had the Bacon Cheeseburger with potato salad which he said was really good. Definitely recommend!
I had bacon cheeseburger and it was outstanding.  It was complemented with an order of homemade mac and cheese. I absolutely loved it!!!
5 stars for burger (I tried bbq texas) and stuff :)
Among the best burgers I've ever had. A must visit for any trip to the French Quarter.
Burgers are excellent
Burgers are amazing and huge! Super sweet bartender, nice laid back atmosphere! Would definitely come back!
Great burger, one of the best we ever had, only down side, no fries and it's really small, only three booths and about 12-15 bar stools
Great place if you're looking for something to eat other than gumbo and seafood. Prices don't completely break the bank either. Delicious baked potato. Only con is its 21+ because it's a bar.
The burger was very good! I was surprised by the baked potato that comes with it as a side. It was gigantic and super delicious!
It's great food! Good inexpensive comfort food. Perfect hangovers! Will be returning to this lil diamond this summer while visiting charming new orleans!!
Great dive bar

When I ordered my burger well done I expected tough and burnt as usual, I was highly surprised when the burger was so tender it fell apart in my mouth. Awesome burgers and they are BIG. My tiny stomach couldn't handle half. Baked potatoes are soft and done right when plenty of toppings. Hands down, the best NO burger around. Also fast and friendly service. HIGHLY RECOMMEND.
Dive bar with delicious food and classic rock n roll on the box.
The best burgers and potatoes for the $$...and great staff! Save a few bucks eating here then hit up Emeril's NOLA before you leave town. :D

Slap ya Mama good burgers, great mac'n cheese, and fantastic service! Try their homemade hot sauce and ask about "The Barrel". If you love a good old bar with character, great food, and smooth drinks, then this is the place for you!

The quality of the burgers and food are great. Not too bad in price. Our server was nice but very spotty. The only complaint is that one of the guys from the kitchen brings you the food and he brought it incorrect and refused to take it back. We had to call him back and he barely fixed the issue. Seemed like he had a rough day by his attitude. There's other good places for lunch with a happier staff
The burger was fabulous!
Do it, Burgers are amazing

Waited an hour and half while other guests that ordered after us got their food. Bartender/waitress argued with us when we told her we ready to leave and to take the food off our tab. Burgers looked good, but service was terrible.

Burgers were amazing! It's really strange that they don't serve french fries with them but baked potatoes.. which were very yummy... mac n cheese us just pasta... not very cheesy at all... peanut butter bacon burger was very interesting! You have to try it! Service was good... great experience!
Like everyone else has said...the burger is legit, the place is divy and I like it.

Went here on a recommendation from a local. Good call! Head upstairs and order a burger with Mac & Cheese on the side. It's all made fresh and tastes delicious! They're open late too so this is a great alternative to some fast food place nearby. Highly recommended!

Loved this place.  Fabulous burger, wonderful choice of sides like macaroni and cheese, baked potato that were really nicely done.  It was bloody hot that day and my daughter jokingly asked for their biggest bucket of Coke, the bartender came back with a cup that was huge.  Still enjoying the hot sauce that we bought there made from peppers the owner grows, nummy stuff.
Peanut butter and bacon burger is awesome! Just had it and highly recommend.
had the best bloody mary and the best time on sexual harrassment Friday! LOL. SO fun. My burger was also cooked to perfection!
The hamburger was as great as others have posted.  Service was reasonably fast for a downtown place.
Great burgers, they were huge!!! Cheddar bacon avocado yum yum. Potato was great too. They do not skimp on the toppings at all. Full overload.
Good

Best hamburger in the whole world!  For years I have been trying to find a better one in whatever other country or state I'm in and nothing ever beats it!  And every time I go back, I eat one and its always just as good!  It seems like a place you wouldn't pick for dinner to some people, but TRUST me its the best hamburger you'll ever have, so don't miss out!
Best place ive been 2. all the food was fresh but thats Prob coz we got there just after they opened.  Staff were really nice as well.
Top flight burgers!
A huge surprise loved the peanut butter hamburger crazy!
Great hamburger.   Definitely worth the time and the money.

Poor management. They swop out 100% of the staff, and when it gets written about in an article, the pressure other businesses  to fire the person. They are part of the reason the dungen (ye ol dungeon) is crappy now too

Really, no REALLY tasty burgers! Order their special Yo Mama's Mega One Pound Burger and don't worry if the waitress, who is by the way really friendly, says that it's too big. You won't be able to se how it's gone from your plate directly to your stomach.

We saw Yo Mama on a “Best Hamburger in NOLA” list and we totally agree.  Not what we came to New Orleans for but we're certainly glad we went.  Our mushroom, bacon cheeseburgers were absolutely delicious.  And beautiful – why we didn't take a picture we'll never know.  Not a fancy place by any means, just a bar and grill with an amazing burger.

Awesome burger spot! The restaurant is two stories, the first floor gets really crowded but the second floor has much more room. The second floor also gives off a weird ambience, it's practically red, although I like it. I tried the cheddar cheese burger and had them add some grilled jalapeños for extra spice. Let me tell you, it was delicious! I will most definitely have to come back here. I only dealt with the bartender upstairs, but service was exceptionally SLOW. She took forever to make drinks and wasn't very attentive. If it wasn't for the great burgers, it would have been a horrible experience.

They stole my credit card information and charged me 6 months later!  It was likely someone from my room, but at very least they should check ID when taking a CC! When I called to ask a manager for an explanation or at very least, a comped meal since I've NEVER eaten here before, I was rudely hung up on!

Recommended by a local, this place has fantastic hamburgers!  We told ourselves we would try to eat food authentic to the area but couldn't resist their Bacon Cheeseburger.   It was DELICIOUS!  Count this place as a must-try in the French Quarter.
an absolute joke! service terrible, food took over an hour to arrive, given wrong order and was still expected to pay for it! DO NOT WASTE YOUR TIME OR MONEY! You will regret it.......guaranteed.

The food was good! One of the best peanut butter burgers ever. But it ended up costing me $350 when my cc# was "stolen" there and used online to buy $350 worth of items. This was in 2011, so I hope whom ever did the deed is not employed there now. It was the only place I used my CC in NOLA, so it had to have been one of the wait staff that was there that day.
we've been waiting gut 50 minutes and still haven't even received a salad

There is a question about Yo Mamma's that anyone who has been there will ask. Is it a burger joint pretending to be a dive bar or a dive bar pretending to be a burger joint. Don't let the numerous bar stools, laid back decor, and friendly bartenders fool you, Yo Mamma's is a burger joint.  Tucked away on a side street just a block off of Bourbon Street, Yo Mamma's brings one thing to the city of New Orleans that every downtown area needs. A quality late night eating spot. They are open late and serve what I would call the city's best burger. Their burgers are big, juicy, and made from quality meet. And they don't short you on the availability of topings either. From your classics like cheese and mushrooms, too some more unconventional topics like bacon and peanut butter (I know but strangely it works), they have something for every partially happy, hungry, partially intoxiacted person wondering the french quarter. Also they don't serve fries, so you get your choice of side salad or loaded baked potato. Also try the Gumbo, but be warned the gumbo goes fast so they may not have any left by the time you get there.
Cool place and pretty chill. Good burgers and a decent beer list.

BEST gumbo in the French Quarter! Try it with the alligator and crawfish sausage on the side. As a native of New Orleans, I can tell you this is the real deal - my kind of comfort food :-) The atmosphere is relaxed, the food is excellent and the prices are very reasonable. The kitchen and bar staff are also really friendly. What's not to love? This is one of my must-visit haunts whenever I drop back into the Big Easy.

Leave it to NOLA to tuck away one of the best burgers in the city at the back of the upstairs bar of dingy locale. However, the burgers are juicy and big, something most places cannot follow up on. The caviar burger was great, but the peanut butter is the one to try if you are looking for a good time, big guy.
Best burgers in NOLA & more tequila varieties than you can shake a salt shaker at! Go. NOW.

They have an interesting variety of burgers, but it's pretty much all novelty. I have always found their burgers to be pretty bland and, I suspect, pre-made, frozen patties. They just slap enough peanut butter and other stuff on them to mask it. Never been impressed.
Best burgers in NOLA. Order them medium.
Awesome blue cheese and avocado burger! And, the baked potatoes are ginormous. So glad our ghost tour app led us here... we could've walked right by and settled for some bad Bourbon Street burger.
One of the best burgers I've ever had! Great service and they had an improv comedy show that was great too. Highly recommended!
Some of the best burgers in town.  Also, has a great list of tequilas.  The jukebox is great.
awesome burgers and tequila
This place is amazing! I vote this hamburger joint over Port of Call any day. The service may be slow when the bar is busy but the food have never disappointed! I highly suggest.
best burger in NOLA, yo mama jokes on the receipts, playboy pics in the bathroom, this place is awesome

Some of the best burgers in New Orleans and you don't even have to stand in line!  Be prepared to take a nap afterward because these burgers will hurt you in a good way.  They don't serve fries, but the bake potatoes are much tastier, especially with cheese and chili.
great burgers...
